00:20:16.924 --> 00:20:19.552
What? Mother. Mother! Hi!

253
00:20:21.220 --> 00:20:22.722
Mother, I caught
some field mice for your dinner.

254
00:20:22.805 --> 00:20:25.474
I left them by the... Okay.

255
00:20:27.351 --> 00:20:29.228
Hey, Kovu.

256
00:20:29.520 --> 00:20:31.522
Wanna fight?

257
00:20:33.149 --> 00:20:36.277
You were supposed to be watching him!

258
00:20:37.111 --> 00:20:39.780
It's not his fault. I went off on my own.

259
00:20:39.864 --> 00:20:41.949
-What were you doing?
-Nothing.

260
00:20:42.032 --> 00:20:44.618
-Who has made us Outsiders?
-Simba.

261
00:20:44.785 --> 00:20:47.329
-Who killed Scar?
-Simba.

262
00:20:47.538 --> 00:20:51.709
What have I told you about them?

263
00:20:52.334 --> 00:20:54.044
I'm sorry, Mother.

264
00:20:54.128 --> 00:20:56.255
She didn't seem so bad.

265
00:20:56.338 --> 00:20:59.341
-I thought we could be...
-Friends?

266
00:21:00.050 --> 00:21:02.928
You thought you'd get to the daughter,

267
00:21:03.012 --> 00:21:06.640
and Simba would welcome you
with open arms?

268
00:21:06.932 --> 00:21:09.310
What an idea!

269
00:21:10.644 --> 00:21:13.606
What an idea.

270
00:21:14.607 --> 00:21:17.359
You brilliant child.

271
00:21:17.443 --> 00:21:20.154
I'm so proud of you.

272
00:21:20.237 --> 00:21:26.994
You have the same conniving mind
that made Scar so powerful.

273
00:21:41.175 --> 00:21:42.551
Chosen One.

274
00:21:51.393 --> 00:21:53.729
I now see the path

275
00:21:53.813 --> 00:21:58.901
to our glorious return to power!

276
00:21:59.902 --> 00:22:01.570
-But I don't want...
-Hush!

277
00:22:02.279 --> 00:22:04.490
Hush, my little one.

278
00:22:05.491 --> 00:22:09.161
You must be exhausted.

279
00:22:10.412 --> 00:22:13.374
<i>♪ Sleep, my little Kovu ♪</i>

280
00:22:13.874 --> 00:22:16.836
<i>♪ Let your dreams take wing ♪</i>

281
00:22:17.586 --> 00:22:21.507
<i>♪ One day when you're big and strong ♪</i>

282
00:22:21.590 --> 00:22:25.845
<i>♪ You will be a king ♪</i>

283
00:22:26.345 --> 00:22:29.014
-Good night.
-Good night, my little prince.

284
00:22:29.265 --> 00:22:33.269
Tomorrow your training intensifies.

285
00:22:33.727 --> 00:22:38.649
<i>♪ I've been exiled, persecuted ♪
♪ Left alone with no defence ♪</i>

286
00:22:39.149 --> 00:22:43.946
<i>♪ When I think of what that brute did ♪
♪ I get a little tense ♪</i>

287
00:22:44.154 --> 00:22:49.118
<i>♪ But I dream a dream so pretty ♪
♪ That I don't feel so depressed ♪</i>

288
00:22:49.243 --> 00:22:54.248
<i>♪ 'Cause it soothes my inner kitty ♪
♪ And it helps me get some rest ♪</i>

289
00:22:54.415 --> 00:22:56.959
<i>♪ The sound of Simba's dying gasp ♪</i>

290
00:22:57.793 --> 00:23:00.921
<i>♪ His daughter squealing in my grasp ♪</i>

291
00:23:01.797 --> 00:23:05.175
<i>♪ His lioness' mournful cry ♪</i>

292
00:23:05.593 --> 00:23:08.304
<i>♪ That's my lullaby ♪</i>

293
00:23:09.471 --> 00:23:14.351
<i>♪ Now the past I've tried forgetting ♪
♪ And my foes I could forgive ♪</i>

294
00:23:14.643 --> 00:23:19.481
<i>♪ Trouble is I know it's petty ♪
♪ But I hate to let them live ♪</i>

295
00:23:19.565 --> 00:23:24.403
<i>♪ So you found yourself somebody ♪
♪ Who'll chase Simba up a tree ♪</i>

296
00:23:24.486 --> 00:23:28.824
<i>♪ Oh, the battle may be bloody ♪
♪ But that kind of works for me ♪</i>

297
00:23:29.992 --> 00:23:32.828
<i>♪ The melody of angry growls ♪</i>

298
00:23:33.537 --> 00:23:36.415
<i>♪ A counterpoint of painful howls ♪</i>

299
00:23:37.583 --> 00:23:40.836
<i>♪ A symphony of death. Oh, my... ♪</i>

300
00:23:41.170 --> 00:23:44.506
<i>♪ That's my lullaby ♪</i>

301
00:23:45.132 --> 00:23:48.844
<i>♪ Scar is gone, but Zira's still around ♪</i>

302
00:23:49.428 --> 00:23:52.348
<i>♪ To love this little lad ♪</i>

303
00:23:53.182 --> 00:23:56.602
<i>♪ Till he learns to be a killer ♪</i>

304
00:23:56.685 --> 00:24:00.814
<i>♪ With a lust for being bad ♪</i>

305
00:24:04.026 --> 00:24:06.153
Sleep, you little termite.

306
00:24:06.236 --> 00:24:08.989
<i>♪ I mean, precious little thing ♪</i>

307
00:24:09.073 --> 00:24:12.242
<i>♪ One day when you're big and strong ♪</i>

308
00:24:12.326 --> 00:24:14.954
<i>♪ You will be a king ♪</i>

309
00:24:17.623 --> 00:24:20.334
<i>♪ The pounding of the drums of war ♪</i>

310
00:24:20.876 --> 00:24:23.420
<i>♪ The thrill of Kovu's mighty roar ♪</i>

311
00:24:23.712 --> 00:24:26.548
<i>♪ -The joy of vengeance ♪
♪ -Testify ♪</i>

312
00:24:26.715 --> 00:24:28.550
<i>♪ I can hear the cheering ♪</i>

313
00:24:28.717 --> 00:24:30.386
<i>♪ Kovu, what a guy ♪</i>

314
00:24:30.552 --> 00:24:35.224
<i>♪ Payback time is nearing ♪
♪ And then our flag will fly ♪</i>

315
00:24:35.724 --> 00:24:38.602
<i>♪ Against a blood-red sky ♪</i>

316
00:24:39.687 --> 00:24:46.402
<i>♪ That's my lullaby ♪</i>

317
00:25:00.666 --> 00:25:05.337
Mufasa,
every day Kiara grows more beautiful,

318
00:25:05.546 --> 00:25:10.217
into a queen that will someday
make us all very proud.

319
00:25:11.093 --> 00:25:14.555
But this cub Kovu grows stronger,

320
00:25:14.638 --> 00:25:17.391
and Zira fills his heart with hate.

321
00:25:18.100 --> 00:25:20.144
I'm very worried, Mufasa.

322
00:25:20.227 --> 00:25:22.604
Things are not going well, no.

323
00:25:26.942 --> 00:25:28.694
You have a plan?

324
00:25:31.280 --> 00:25:32.614
What?

325
00:25:37.327 --> 00:25:42.082
Kovu. Kiara. Together?

326
00:25:43.333 --> 00:25:45.127
This is the plan?

327
00:25:45.544 --> 00:25:48.130
Are you crazy? This will never work.

328
00:25:48.505 --> 00:25:51.800
Mufasa, you been up there too long.
Your head is in the clouds.

329
00:25:53.802 --> 00:25:57.347
Okay, okay, okay.
Okay, all right, okay!

330
00:25:57.431 --> 00:26:00.809
I don't think this is going to work,
but I trust you.

331
00:26:00.893 --> 00:26:03.645
I just hope you know
what you are doing.

332
00:26:12.571 --> 00:26:15.282
You are ready.

333
00:26:17.785 --> 00:26:19.328
Nice.

334
00:26:19.411 --> 00:26:21.330
Very nice.

335
00:26:24.583 --> 00:26:28.545
You have the same blackness
in your soul that Scar had.

336
00:26:29.004 --> 00:26:31.006
What is your destiny?

337
00:26:31.173 --> 00:26:35.677
I will avenge Scar.
Take his place in the Pride Lands.

338
00:26:35.886 --> 00:26:38.097
Yes. What have I taught you?

339
00:26:38.305 --> 00:26:40.432
Simba is the enemy.

340
00:26:40.516 --> 00:26:43.894
And what must you do?

341
00:26:44.186 --> 00:26:46.814
I must kill him.

342
00:27:01.954 --> 00:27:03.997
This is Kiara's first hunt.

343
00:27:06.166 --> 00:27:07.292
There she is!

344
00:27:09.002 --> 00:27:10.129
Kiara.

345
00:27:14.716 --> 00:27:17.594
-You can do it.
-It's your day.

346
00:27:17.928 --> 00:27:21.223
-Your first time.
-My, how you've grown.

347
00:27:26.436 --> 00:27:28.605
You'll do just fine.

348
00:27:29.439 --> 00:27:34.403
Daddy? You have to promise
to let me do this on my own. Promise?

349
00:27:37.656 --> 00:27:40.200
All right. I promise.

350
00:28:07.644 --> 00:28:10.439
Make sure she doesn't get hurt.

351
00:28:35.380 --> 00:28:38.967
This place is even creepier
since the hyenas ran off.

352
00:28:41.261 --> 00:28:44.181
I'm not scared, okay?

353
00:28:47.100 --> 00:28:49.978
I just don't know why
we have to be here, that's all.

354
00:28:50.103 --> 00:28:54.149
If Kovu is so special,
why does he need us?

355
00:28:54.233 --> 00:28:55.817
I never even had a chance.

356
00:29:01.823 --> 00:29:04.576
That's it! Come on.

357
00:29:04.701 --> 00:29:07.537
Kiara has started her hunt.
We have to move quickly.

358
00:29:12.334 --> 00:29:13.835
Fire!

359
00:29:43.949 --> 00:29:46.243
Tango Charlie Alpha,
what's your position?

360
00:29:47.661 --> 00:29:51.707
Upright, head turned
slightly to the left, tail erect.

361
00:29:52.040 --> 00:29:53.500
Why do I bother?

362
00:30:20.569 --> 00:30:22.696
This must be where
the deer and the antelope play.

363
00:30:28.368 --> 00:30:30.412
Timon, what are you doing here?

364
00:30:30.579 --> 00:30:31.997
Shopping!

365
00:30:32.080 --> 00:30:35.751
We thought a nice pelt for the den,
some throw pillows, a little potpourri...

366
00:30:35.917 --> 00:30:37.336
My father sent you.

367
00:30:37.419 --> 00:30:40.047
After he promised
to let me do this on my own. He lied!

368
00:30:40.130 --> 00:30:43.008
No. He just doesn't want you to get hurt.

369
00:30:43.175 --> 00:30:45.385
I should have known
he'd never give me a real chance.

370
00:30:46.595 --> 00:30:47.971
I'll do this on my own!

371
00:30:48.055 --> 00:30:50.182
Away from the Pride Lands.

372
00:30:50.974 --> 00:30:54.936
-Hey! Wait! Come back!
-Come back here! Kiara!

373
00:30:55.062 --> 00:30:56.605
Kiara, come back!

374
00:30:57.773 --> 00:30:59.191
She's gone again.

375
00:30:59.274 --> 00:31:02.069
Somebody's gotta get
a beeper for this kid.

376
00:31:13.330 --> 00:31:15.624
Let's light fires!

377
00:31:21.296 --> 00:31:25.717
<i>♪ Roasty toasty princess
Roasty toasty princess ♪</i>

378
00:31:26.551 --> 00:31:29.054
Hey, is it hot in here or is that just me?

379
00:31:29.262 --> 00:31:30.847
Fire!

380
00:31:34.309 --> 00:31:35.394
Come on.

381
00:32:03.630 --> 00:32:06.049
The plan is in motion.

382
00:32:06.133 --> 00:32:07.300
Go!

383
00:32:13.056 --> 00:32:16.268
Don't worry, Simba. She'll be fine.

384
00:32:16.351 --> 00:32:17.811
What could happen?

385
00:32:19.354 --> 00:32:22.065
No. No! Kiara!

386
00:32:23.817 --> 00:32:26.528
Zazu, fly ahead. Find her.

387
00:34:00.872 --> 00:34:02.457
I must tell Simba!

388
00:34:13.426 --> 00:34:14.469
Where am I?

389
00:34:15.178 --> 00:34:18.348
You're safe. In the Pride Lands.

390
00:34:18.515 --> 00:34:21.393
The Pride Lands? No!

391
00:34:21.518 --> 00:34:24.062
Why'd you bring me here?
Who do you think you are?

392
00:34:25.105 --> 00:34:27.524
I think I'm the one
that just saved your life.

393
00:34:27.607 --> 00:34:30.026
Look, I had everything under control.

394
00:34:30.235 --> 00:34:31.653
Not from where I'm standing.

395
00:34:31.820 --> 00:34:33.154
Then move downwind.

396
00:34:43.665 --> 00:34:45.417
What are you doing?

397
00:34:47.127 --> 00:34:48.169
Kovu?

398
00:34:49.629 --> 00:34:51.172
Kiara!

399
00:34:52.674 --> 00:34:54.634
Kiara, you're all right.

400
00:34:54.718 --> 00:34:56.428
Father, how could you
break your promise?

401
00:34:56.511 --> 00:34:59.055
It's a good thing I did. I almost lost you.

402
00:34:59.222 --> 00:35:00.932
No more hunts for you, not ever.

403
00:35:01.141 --> 00:35:03.852
But I was doing just fine.
Even before Kovu...

404
00:35:04.060 --> 00:35:05.687
Kovu?

405
00:35:07.480 --> 00:35:09.024
Simba!

406
00:35:09.524 --> 00:35:11.610
Hey! You!

407
00:35:11.860 --> 00:35:15.363
How dare you save
the king's daughter?

408
00:35:15.822 --> 00:35:18.199
You saved her? Why?

409
00:35:18.783 --> 00:35:21.745
-I humbly ask to join your pride.
-No!

410
00:35:21.828 --> 00:35:23.955
You were banished
with the other Outsiders.

411
00:35:24.039 --> 00:35:27.250
I have left the Outsiders. I'm a rogue.

412
00:35:27.459 --> 00:35:30.045
Judge me now for who I am.

413
00:35:31.171 --> 00:35:34.716
Or am I to be blamed
for a crime I didn't commit?

414
00:35:38.637 --> 00:35:41.556
Simba, you owe him
your daughter's life.

415
00:35:42.849 --> 00:35:45.977
Yes, sire. Clearly we are in his debt.

416
00:35:46.061 --> 00:35:49.397
And royal protocol demands
that all debts be paid.

417
00:35:49.481 --> 00:35:52.317
Though in this case,
you might want to make an exception.

418
00:35:57.447 --> 00:36:00.325
My father's law will prevail.

419
00:36:00.492 --> 00:36:03.328
For now, I reserve judgement.

420
00:36:03.411 --> 00:36:05.455
We'll see who you really are.

421
00:36:09.084 --> 00:36:11.127
Riffraff.

422
00:36:59.175 --> 00:37:00.635
Hey.

423
00:37:01.928 --> 00:37:03.972
Thanks for saving me today.

424
00:37:04.055 --> 00:37:07.392
What kind of hunter
are you anyway, Princess?

425
00:37:07.475 --> 00:37:09.060
You almost got yourself killed out there.

426
00:37:09.144 --> 00:37:10.145
What?

427
00:37:10.228 --> 00:37:13.022
You wouldn't last
three days on your own.

428
00:37:13.857 --> 00:37:16.317
And I suppose you could teach me?

429
00:37:16.693 --> 00:37:18.236
Yeah.

430
00:37:18.737 --> 00:37:20.822
-Kiara!
-Coming.

431
00:37:23.658 --> 00:37:26.745
All right! Impress me.

432
00:37:26.828 --> 00:37:28.413
We start at dawn.

433
00:37:32.459 --> 00:37:34.669
I look forward to it.

434
00:37:40.508 --> 00:37:43.094
Did you see that? He let her go!

435
00:37:43.178 --> 00:37:44.721
-If that were me, I...
-Hush.

436
00:37:44.804 --> 00:37:46.848
The fire rescue worked perfectly,

437
00:37:46.931 --> 00:37:48.266
and Simba fell for it.

438
00:37:48.349 --> 00:37:51.811
Now, the closer Kovu
gets to the daughter,

439
00:37:52.020 --> 00:37:55.356
the closer he gets to Simba.

440
00:37:56.191 --> 00:37:59.778
And once he has Simba alone...

441
00:38:10.955 --> 00:38:14.417
Simba! Simba!

442
00:38:15.043 --> 00:38:17.462
-Help me!
-Father!

443
00:38:23.301 --> 00:38:25.053
No! Dad!

444
00:38:26.095 --> 00:38:28.348
Just a little farther...

445
00:38:30.600 --> 00:38:33.812
Gotcha! Trust me.

446
00:38:34.270 --> 00:38:35.980
Simba!

447
00:38:37.690 --> 00:38:40.068
No!

448
00:38:40.568 --> 00:38:42.612
Scar.

449
00:38:45.740 --> 00:38:47.283
Kovu?

450
00:38:48.201 --> 00:38:50.119
No!

451
00:39:37.876 --> 00:39:39.752
Good morning.

452
00:39:40.128 --> 00:39:42.297
I'm ready for my first lesson.

453
00:39:42.422 --> 00:39:44.048
I surprised you, huh?

454
00:39:46.134 --> 00:39:48.469
Hey, come on. Let's go.

455
00:40:10.950 --> 00:40:13.411
Three, two, one...

456
00:40:13.786 --> 00:40:15.538
Gotcha!

457
00:40:17.248 --> 00:40:19.375
You could hear me, huh?

458
00:40:19.751 --> 00:40:21.836
Only a lot.

459
00:40:23.004 --> 00:40:26.007
You're still breathing too hard. Relax.

460
00:40:26.215 --> 00:40:30.970
Feel the earth under your paws,
so it doesn't shift and make noise.

461
00:40:36.309 --> 00:40:39.395
Watch the master and learn.

462
00:40:46.819 --> 00:40:48.446
Don't eat me, please.

463
00:40:49.113 --> 00:40:52.283
I never really met your tyrant...
I mean, Scar. Scar.

464
00:40:52.367 --> 00:40:54.035
Heck of a guy. A little moody, but...

465
00:40:54.535 --> 00:40:57.372
Timon, what are you doing here?

466
00:40:57.580 --> 00:41:00.249
Kiara, thank goodness!

467
00:41:00.333 --> 00:41:02.835
Hey, for once, we're not following you.

468
00:41:02.919 --> 00:41:06.214
This just happens to be the best
smorgasbord in the Pride Lands.

469
00:41:06.464 --> 00:41:08.466
Bugs everywhere.

470
00:41:08.549 --> 00:41:11.719
But you don't call
for a reservation and...

471
00:41:11.886 --> 00:41:15.556
Get outta here, you scavengers!
Go on! Shoo! Shoo!

472
00:41:28.486 --> 00:41:31.447
Timon! I'm getting tired.

473
00:41:31.531 --> 00:41:33.282
I gotta lose some pounds.

474
00:41:34.075 --> 00:41:36.369
Shoo! Go on! Shoo! Shoo!

475
00:41:37.161 --> 00:41:39.789
Hey, maybe he could help.
Do you think?

476
00:41:39.872 --> 00:41:42.667
Shoo! Yeah, there's an idea.

477
00:41:42.750 --> 00:41:44.752
Right. Let the vicious Outsider...

478
00:41:45.086 --> 00:41:47.922
Hey! Wait! I have an idea.

479
00:41:49.090 --> 00:41:51.217
-What if he helps?
-What?

480
00:41:51.509 --> 00:41:52.635
You wanna lend a voice?

481
00:41:56.264 --> 00:41:57.932
Roar! Work with me!

482
00:41:59.267 --> 00:42:00.601
Like this.

483
00:42:04.856 --> 00:42:06.441
Come on. Do it again. Do it again.

484
00:42:10.778 --> 00:42:14.198
Why are we doing this?
What's the point of this training?

485
00:42:14.282 --> 00:42:17.160
Training? This is just for fun!

486
00:42:18.453 --> 00:42:19.495
Fun?

487
00:42:20.621 --> 00:42:23.916
Kid, you gotta get out more often. Fun!

488
00:43:00.661 --> 00:43:02.413
Hey, rhino!

489
00:43:10.296 --> 00:43:12.006
What a blast!

490
00:43:12.590 --> 00:43:13.674
Sorry.

491
00:43:14.801 --> 00:43:16.135
You're okay, kid.

492
00:43:16.219 --> 00:43:18.221
-Hey!
-You're okay.

493
00:43:20.014 --> 00:43:23.893
Pardon me.
That's it, that's it, that's it!

494
00:43:29.649 --> 00:43:31.317
Sorry.

495
00:43:33.569 --> 00:43:35.530
Hey. Are you two coming or what?

496
00:43:43.037 --> 00:43:45.123
-Do you see that?
-What?

497
00:43:45.540 --> 00:43:48.751
-Wow. Look at that. It's really pretty.
-Yeah.

498
00:43:49.752 --> 00:43:52.130
You're right. Look!

499
00:43:52.547 --> 00:43:54.215
There's one
that looks like a baby rabbit.

500
00:43:54.841 --> 00:43:57.343
-See the fluffy tail?
-Yeah.

501
00:43:57.927 --> 00:43:59.470
Hey! There's one that looks like

502
00:43:59.554 --> 00:44:02.223
two lions killing each other
for a scrap of meat.

503
00:44:03.224 --> 00:44:06.394
-I've never done this before.
-Really?

504
00:44:06.477 --> 00:44:09.438
